Hi, I am a [Qt for Python](https://doc.qt.io/qtforpython-6/) developer. A while ago, I discussed in the p4a discord channel about the possibility of adding a new bootstrap that uses Qt instead of SDL2, and I had a positive response from you guys. This would be the first among possibly many series of patches.

The Qt boostrap would enable PySide to use the entire p4a infrastructure to package PySide application to Android .apk. There would also be recipes for PySide6 and [shiboken6](https://doc.qt.io/qtforpython-6/shiboken6/index.html), but this would live inside [PySide repository.](https://code.qt.io/cgit/pyside/pyside-setup.git/tree/sources/pyside-tools/deploy_lib/android/recipes)

**How would we use p4a and use this new bootstrap?**

We provide a tool called _pyside6-android-deploy_ which is basically a interface to setup the recipes for PySide6 and shiboken6, and create a custom _buildozer.spec_ file with all the dependencies added. The tool then further calls "_buildozer android debug_" which uses the created _buildozer.spec_ file. The entire working of this tool is detailed here: [https://www.qt.io/blog/taking-qt-for-python-to-android](https://www.qt.io/blog/taking-qt-for-python-to-android). That said, the tool is ofcourse still under technical preview. 

Among other attributes from `_buildozer.spec_`, `_pyside6-android-deploy_` sets the following important ones:
```
requirements = python3,shiboken6,PySide6

// _we need android_ndk and android_sdk to cross compile PySide6 and shiboken6 to wheels compatible with a specific Android architecture_
android.ndk_path = /home/shyamnath/.pyside6_android_deploy/android-ndk/android-ndk-r25c
android.sdk_path = /home/shyamnath/.pyside6_android_deploy/android-sdk

// _currently uses my fork_
p4a.fork = shyamnathp
p4a.branch = pyside_support_3
p4a.bootstrap = qt

// _this directory would contain the directory with the PySide6 and shiboken6 recipes after pyside6-android-deploy uses_
// _jinja2 to create them_
p4a.local_recipes = /test_project/deployment/recipes
android.permissions = {extra_permissions depending on the Qt modules used in application}
android.add_jars = {all Qt jars required by the application. One of these jars contains QtActivity java class which PythonAcitivity class is derived from.}

// _3 new cli arguments have been added to p4a to populate `pythonforandroid/bootstraps/qt/build/templates/libs.tmpl.xml` which // would be used by Qt_
p4a.extra_args = --qt-libs={Qt modules used} --load-local-libs={mostly for plugins from Qt} --init-classes={Qt java class names to be loaded}
`
```
**What does the recipes do?**

Since we create PySide6 and shiboken6 wheels for Android, the only thing the recipes does is to unzip the wheels into the `site-packages` of the target python.

